200 g Mixed Mushrooms
227 g Sugar Snap Peas
1 tbsp Zesty Garlic Blend
1 unit(s) Red Onion
227 g Broccoli
28 g Almonds, sliced
½ tbsp Worcestershire Sauce
2 tbsp Garlic Spread
1 unit(s) Lemon
2 tbsp Oil*
¼ tsp Salt*
¼ tsp Pepper*
1 tbsp Butter*

Trim sugar snap peas.
Cut broccoli into bite-sized pieces.
Quarter mushrooms.
Peel, then cut onion into 1/2-inch slices.
Zest lemon, then juice half the lemon. Cut remaining lemon into wedges.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter. Swirl the pan to melt.
Add almonds and Worcestershire sauce.
Reduce heat to medium-low. Cook, stirring constantly, until almonds are golden, 3-4 min. (TIP: Keep your eye on them so they don't burn!)
Remove the pan from heat, add 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) Zesty Garlic Blend. Season with salt and pepper. Stir to coat.
Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate.

Using the same pan (from step 2), increase heat to medium-high.
When hot, add broccoli and 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) water. Cook, stirring occasionally, until water evaporates, 4-5 min. Season with salt and pepper.
Transfer broccoli to a baking dish and cover to keep warm.

Add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil to the same pan.
When hot, add onions. Cook, stirring often, until softened, 1-2 min.
Add sugar snap peas. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender-crisp, 3-4 min.
Season with salt and pepper.
Transfer to the same baking dish with broccoli. Cover to keep warm.

Add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil to the same pan, then add mushrooms. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, 3-4 min. Season with salt and pepper.
Add to baking dish with veggies.

Meanwhile, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) garlic spread and remaining Zesty Garlic Blend to a small microwaveable bowl. Microwave until garlic spread is melted, 30 sec.
Once melted, stir in lemon zest and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper.
Pour lemon-garlic sauce over veggies, then stir to coat.
Keep veggies in oven until ready to eat.
Top with spiced almonds before serving.